several commonly harvested life-forms. Given the high variance in estimates for most NTFP species, $\lambda$ does not provide a precise assessment of harvest impacts. We recommend that managers consider the combined elasticity-LTRE analysis in addition to $\lambda$ in making management decisions for NTFP. NTFP research that accounts for environmental drivers of population dynamics in addition to harvest should be prioritized. {\textcopyright} 2011 The Authors. Journal of Applied Ecology {\textcopyright} 2011 British Ecological Society.},
author = {Schmidt, Isabel B. and Mandle, Lisa and Ticktin, Tamara and Gaoue, Orou G.},
doi = {10.1111/j.1365-2664.2011.01999.x},
file = {:Users/ema/Library/Application Support/Mendeley Desktop/Downloaded/Schmidt et al. - 2011 - What do matrix population models reveal about the sustainability of non-timber forest product harvest.pdf:pdf},
