Sandy beaches are better breeding sites for little terns because they are closer to the see, where little terns can fish preys that are better for the chicks' growth. The main reasons why little terns reproduce poorly is due to human disturbance and predation. However, conservation strategies to protect little terns have been applied and caused a better reproductive success.},
