DISCUSSION
MPM worked only for one of the two populations and the transient analysis didn't work at all.
The major problem about MPM is that it assumes that vital rates will remain the same in the future. Reasons why the author thinks that this is not the case:
1) A too small sampling size has been considered to estimate the survival probability. This is true especially for rare species. It is important to report also the confidence limits.
2) More samples should be taken. This is because it's possible then to take sthocasticity more into account. 
