If you want to compare two different populations, the environment and the density dependent effects should be really similar.
Lamda just estimates the tendence of the population growth in the future. It's possible that in the near future the population will decline and then die. It depends from the initial composition of the population. It provides an example of why 3 different populations behave in different ways even if the matrix is the same. 
